</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Theopea bicolor, T. bicoloroides sp. nov., and T. mouhoti. A T. bicolor, male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C T. bicolor, female, dorsal view D T. bicoloroides sp. nov., male, dorsal view E Same, ventral view F T. bicoloroides sp. nov., female, dorsal view G T. mouhoti, male H Same, ventral view I T. mouhoti, female, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380656" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">1A-F</figureCitation>
) can be easily separately from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. mouhoti" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="mouhoti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. mouhoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Theopea bicolor, T. bicoloroides sp. nov., and T. mouhoti. A T. bicolor, male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C T. bicolor, female, dorsal view D T. bicoloroides sp. nov., male, dorsal view E Same, ventral view F T. bicoloroides sp. nov., female, dorsal view G T. mouhoti, male H Same, ventral view I T. mouhoti, female, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380656" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">1G-I</figureCitation>
) by the dark brown or blackish brown head, prothorax, and scutellum, and indistinct ridges in the elytra. Besides, males of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. possess a median elongate sclerite internally in the aedeagus that is covered with transverse rows of hair-like setae (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicolor. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380657" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2C, D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3C, D</figureCitation>
). This differs from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. mouhoti" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="mouhoti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. mouhoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which lacks such hair-like setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Diagnostic characters of Theopea mouhoti. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Same, lateral view E Same, ventral view F Aedeagus, variation, ventral view G Abdominal ventrite VIII H Gonocoxae I Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380659" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">4C, D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1864" authorityName="Kimoto" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Theopea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Theopea bicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Theopea bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by the relatively slender antennae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicolor. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380657" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2A</figureCitation>
) in males (length to width ratios of antennomeres V-X more than 3.0 in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, relatively broader antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3A</figureCitation>
), less than 3.0 in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.), the narrowly rounded apex of the ventral surface of the aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicolor. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380657" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2E</figureCitation>
) (broadly rounded apex of aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3E</figureCitation>
)), endophallic sclerite broad and without longitudinal groove in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicolor. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380657" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2D</figureCitation>
) (dorso-ventrally flattened and with longitudinal groove in lateral view in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3D</figureCitation>
)), and slender notch at apex of gonocoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicolor. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380657" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2G</figureCitation>
) (broad notch at apex of gonocoxae in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3G</figureCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
